387
00:38:58,348 --> 00:39:00,709
[SPEAKER_00]: somewhat of limited staffing across the organization.

388
00:39:00,749 --> 00:39:12,636
[SPEAKER_00]: And it's very difficult to provide, especially for positions that require in-person work, to have people not physically present.

389
00:39:12,756 --> 00:39:25,702
[SPEAKER_00]: If somebody wants to speak with another employee in another office and needs to sit down and meet with them, it's really important that people are here, whether that's a position that, you know,

390
00:39:26,943 --> 00:39:34,086
[SPEAKER_00]: I would call them their customers, so to speak, you know, the customers of the finance department are mostly internal folks.

391
00:39:34,406 --> 00:39:45,030
[SPEAKER_00]: The customers of, say, an outward facing office, like the city clerk's office are typically the public or the treasurer collector, just picking departments that are on this call.

392
00:39:45,350 --> 00:39:48,251
[SPEAKER_00]: Whereas information technology, their customers are internal.

393
00:39:50,032 --> 00:40:05,681
[SPEAKER_00]: Regardless of who the customers are, a lot of times it's almost with our staffing size, it's almost impossible to have the opportunity to have the types of opportunities the state has.

394
00:40:06,201 --> 00:40:15,567
[SPEAKER_00]: The position that Miss Cardello has taken at the state is one that basically Miss Cardello reviews the books of communities and she

395
00:40:16,147 --> 00:40:24,172
[SPEAKER_00]: is their, I think, field agent, if I'm not mistaken, Bob, and that allows complete remote work.

396
00:40:24,393 --> 00:40:27,334
[SPEAKER_00]: It's just something that we can't compete with at that level.

397
00:40:27,414 --> 00:40:30,917
[SPEAKER_00]: It's not something that the city of Medford at this scale can offer.

398
00:40:36,078 --> 00:40:52,133
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, and I get that there are differences in context, and I'm not saying that we should across the board offer remote work, but just the bigger picture thing that I'm interested in is

399
00:40:53,334 --> 00:41:04,625
[SPEAKER_07]: those cases where we have, where we can't seem to keep a position filled, which causes a lot of other issues.

400
00:41:04,685 --> 00:41:14,214
[SPEAKER_07]: So what I'm interested in is, okay, what policies can be changed, what policies can be set to increase retention?

401
00:41:14,314 --> 00:41:14,934
[SPEAKER_07]: And it could be

402
