585
00:56:07,367 --> 00:56:09,207
[SPEAKER_03]: You can get that every two years.

586
00:56:10,068 --> 00:56:17,930
[SPEAKER_03]: That paid for about half of the fiber project itself, maybe a little under half of it, which was a huge win for us.

587
00:56:19,316 --> 00:56:20,517
[SPEAKER_03]: There's another one.

588
00:56:20,537 --> 00:56:25,142
[SPEAKER_03]: It's called the Community Compact IT Infrastructure Grant.

589
00:56:25,162 --> 00:56:25,863
[SPEAKER_03]: We can apply for that.

590
00:56:25,883 --> 00:56:27,364
[SPEAKER_03]: That opens in January or so.

591
00:56:27,384 --> 00:56:28,485
[SPEAKER_03]: I think that's about up to $250,000.

592
00:56:28,565 --> 00:56:29,566
[SPEAKER_03]: Just waiting to see what

593
00:56:41,605 --> 00:56:45,387
[SPEAKER_03]: I don't want to spend it on a $40,000 project, right, that we get the grant and only spend it.

594
00:56:45,467 --> 00:56:46,647
[SPEAKER_03]: We're going to think of something big.

595
00:56:46,687 --> 00:56:51,230
[SPEAKER_03]: Now that's what we end up with, and of course we'll apply and get the money every little bit helps.

596
00:56:52,150 --> 00:56:57,773
[SPEAKER_03]: But if we need to tie it into what we're doing on the finance side somehow or

597
00:56:59,073 --> 00:57:05,980
[SPEAKER_03]: On the side of some other system that needs to get replaced, or bringing in a new system for automation or for something along those lines.

598
00:57:06,441 --> 00:57:13,808
[SPEAKER_03]: So we'll see as the year goes on, I talk to people all the time about what their needs are going forward, what they're thinking about as far as modernization.

599
00:57:14,769 --> 00:57:18,092
[SPEAKER_03]: And then there's some cybersecurity grants too that is

600
00:57:19,385 --> 00:57:27,289
[SPEAKER_03]: problem with them are is that they're not, they're not well written as far as the contracts and the products they chose at the state level.

601
00:57:27,870 --> 00:57:29,971
[SPEAKER_03]: So it really locks you into one path.

602
00:57:30,951 --> 00:57:36,314
[SPEAKER_03]: So in looking through them, I was just like, you know, it's actually going to cost us more money in the long run to

603
00:57:38,068 --> 00:57:52,111
[SPEAKER_03]: replace what we have, the state pays like two years of it, and then you have to go back out on your own, so you have to migrate back again to something else, so that the acquisition and renewal costs outweigh any advantages and really get some of those.

604
00:57:52,832 --> 00:57:53,812
[SPEAKER_03]: But, you know, we're always listening.

605
00:57:53,852 --> 00:57:59,233
[SPEAKER_03]: I talk to all my peers in the surrounding areas, you know, if they hear of anything, I'll share the knowledge, so.

606
00:58:08,319 --> 00:58:09,000
[SPEAKER_09]: Thank you, Rich.

607
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:12,062
[SPEAKER_09]: Just had a couple last questions.

608
