[SPEAKER_03]: No, so it is a really old legacy account.

611
00:58:20,390 --> 00:58:23,953
[SPEAKER_03]: We haven't had copper phones in over 13 years.

612
00:58:24,894 --> 00:58:28,778
[SPEAKER_03]: It was an old account for that, fax lines, things like that.

613
00:58:29,298 --> 00:58:33,922
[SPEAKER_03]: I was using it just to pay for stuff like BIOS internet for buildings and things, but it's like,

614
00:58:34,778 --> 00:58:40,144
[SPEAKER_03]: every year, I'd have to add more money to it from somewhere else because it's only at a $7,000 cap.

615
00:58:40,164 --> 00:58:49,013
[SPEAKER_03]: I was like, well, instead of extending it, I'll just roll it into, I think, put it in computer software or something and just deal with it that way.

616
00:58:50,274 --> 00:58:52,216
[SPEAKER_03]: Just save less paperwork for everyone.

617
00:58:53,758 --> 00:58:54,018
[SPEAKER_03]: Got it.

