651
01:00:45,871 --> 01:00:46,811
[SPEAKER_03]: But yeah, there's not much we can do.

652
01:00:46,851 --> 01:00:49,673
[SPEAKER_03]: The same thing with our service desk.

653
01:00:50,954 --> 01:00:54,197
[SPEAKER_03]: That cost hasn't gone up more than 3% since I've been here.

654
01:00:55,718 --> 01:01:03,283
[SPEAKER_03]: And we do it through, where we started from, they were doing X amount of calls per month from us.

655
01:01:03,824 --> 01:01:05,325
[SPEAKER_03]: I came in and stabilized everything.

656
01:01:05,365 --> 01:01:06,466
[SPEAKER_03]: They're modernizing things.

657
01:01:06,486 --> 01:01:10,609
[SPEAKER_03]: Their call volume has dropped proportionally by quite a bit, almost two thirds.

658
01:01:11,269 --> 01:01:11,830
[SPEAKER_03]: So I'm like, look,

659
01:01:12,590 --> 01:01:20,376
[SPEAKER_03]: keep my costs flat, you guys have then take that savings and move it to, you know, other customers and what have you.

660
01:01:20,416 --> 01:01:22,237
[SPEAKER_03]: So, they're very amenable to that.

661
01:01:23,238 --> 01:01:24,879
[SPEAKER_03]: So, we'll see what goes.

662
01:01:24,899 --> 01:01:28,922
[SPEAKER_03]: We have a really good working relationship, so I don't see that skyrocketing at any point.

663
01:01:30,303 --> 01:01:34,866
[SPEAKER_03]: We also got, you know, when we absorbed the library into the fold, that was no upcharge for that.

664
01:01:36,627 --> 01:01:42,111
[SPEAKER_03]: So, we managed to keep things flat and save a lot of money in areas too.

665
01:01:44,684 --> 01:01:45,385
[SPEAKER_09]: Appreciate that.

666
01:01:46,265 --> 01:01:49,908
[SPEAKER_09]: And I know it's not easy, not a lot of vendors, not a lot of options.

667
01:01:50,028 --> 01:01:54,091
[SPEAKER_09]: So, I understand, understand that conundrum.

668
01:01:54,992 --> 01:01:56,633
[SPEAKER_09]: Last thing just on the actuals.

