[SPEAKER_03]: I mean, it's a 90 year old building.

696
01:03:58,562 --> 01:04:01,283
[SPEAKER_03]: It was made out of concrete on wire mesh.

697
01:04:02,047 --> 01:04:04,529
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, obviously they weren't thinking of Wi-Fi in 1936.

698
01:04:04,849 --> 01:04:21,480
[SPEAKER_03]: So even putting a Wi-Fi, it was definitely like in places like the conference rooms, conference rooms, chambers, and down outside of treasury parking, because a lot of people come in there and immediately pull out their phones.

699
01:04:21,500 --> 01:04:23,782
